The gods bestow upon us a mortal life

198
00:30:01,858 --> 00:30:05,997
But we are true men indeed

199
00:30:05,998 --> 00:30:11,667
A true man dies in the battlefield

200
00:30:11,668 --> 00:30:16,707
and he strides to the heavenly home
of our ancestors

201
00:30:16,708 --> 00:30:24,777
There lies a fertile hunting ground

202
00:30:24,778 --> 00:30:32,087
that can only be guarded by a qualified true man

203
00:30:33,788 --> 00:30:37,857
When he arrives at the heavenly home
of our ancestors

204
00:30:37,858 --> 00:30:42,367
he'll come across a beautiful rainbow bridge

205
00:30:42,368 --> 00:30:47,507
The ancestors' spirits guarding it say.

206
00:30:47,508 --> 00:30:50,707
''Let's take a look at your hands''

207
00:30:50,708 --> 00:30:53,647
When the man opens his hands

208
00:30:53,648 --> 00:31:01,547
we see bloodstains that can never be wiped clean

209
00:31:01,548 --> 00:31:05,247
''Now you're a true man indeed!''
says our ancestors' spirits

210
00:31:10,629 --> 00:31:13,668
Come out, guys!

211
00:31:13,668 --> 00:31:16,737
Bring your weapons!

212
00:31:16,738 --> 00:31:18,667
Come on!

213
00:31:19,968 --> 00:31:25,477
''Go! Go ahead! My hero!''

214
00:31:25,478 --> 00:31:29,747
''Your soul may now enter
the heavenly home of our ancestors

215
00:31:29,748 --> 00:31:36,477
''to guard the hunting ground of honor''

216
00:31:38,318 --> 00:31:40,917
Stop it! It'll never be ignited

217
