Mouna, stop glaring

260
00:37:58,368 --> 00:38:00,237
Ubus..

261
00:38:00,238 --> 00:38:02,797
our ancestors never lost
any of our hunting grounds in the past

262
00:38:04,538 --> 00:38:08,067
I can't believe these intruders
are taking them away from us now

263
00:38:09,718 --> 00:38:12,047
I'll never submit to them

264
00:38:13,548 --> 00:38:15,707
I will never

265
00:38:22,298 --> 00:38:24,787
These are all yours?

266
00:38:29,938 --> 00:38:31,597
I will never!

267
00:38:35,438 --> 00:38:36,467
Mouna!

268
00:38:46,748 --> 00:38:47,777
Stop it!

269
00:38:54,688 --> 00:38:55,957
Mouna!

270
00:38:56,428 --> 00:38:57,357
Mouna!

271
00:39:33,768 --> 00:39:36,667
Hurry up! It's going to rain

272
00:39:42,338 --> 00:39:43,737
Awi!

273
00:39:44,878 --> 00:39:46,237
Awi!

274
00:39:48,178 --> 00:39:49,447
What's wrong?

275
00:39:49,448 --> 00:39:51,107
Are you alright?

276
00:39:53,218 --> 00:39:55,117
What's wrong?

277
00:39:55,118 --> 00:39:56,357
Are you alright?

278
00:39:56,358 --> 00:40:00,987
(Wushe, 1930)

279
00:40:04,498 --> 00:40:07,427
Schools, clinics, grocery stores

280
00:40:07,429 --> 00:40:10,868
post offices, hotels, boardinghouses..

281
00:40:10,868 --> 00:40:12,737
We've managed to civilize

282
00:40:12,739 --> 00:40:16,378
all the Wushe savages

283
00:40:16,378 --> 00:40:19,277
It's not an easy task

284
00:40:19,278 --> 00:40:25,377
Hard to imagine that this was once
the most uncivilized heartland here

285
00:40:26,518 --> 00:40:29,687
Carrying logs..

286
00:40:29,688 --> 00:40:32,287
and walking from the lumberyard uphill to here
takes them a whole day, doesn't it?

287
00:40:32,288 --> 00:40:38,797
Don't worry. These savages are strong

288
00:40:38,798 --> 00:40:44,457
And they're more than happy
to earn some money for millet wine

289
00:40:46,008 --> 00:40:47,627
Come on. This way please

290
00:40:50,508 --> 00:40:51,807
Mr. Satsuka,

291
00:40:51,808 --> 00:40:55,107
how long have you been in Wushe?

292
00:40:55,108 --> 00:40:56,947
Over a decade

293
00:40:56,948 --> 00:41:00,387
So you know this region very well?

294
00:41:00,388 --> 00:41:04,217
Of course. My wife is a savage woman

295
00:41:04,218 --> 00:41:06,827
I know this region like the back of my hand
-It's this bone right here

296
00:41:06,828 --> 00:41:08,757
It hurts so much when you press it

297
00:41:08,759 --> 00:41:10,098
Right here?

298
00:41:10,098 --> 00:41:11,797
Ah! Easy!

299
00:41:11,798 --> 00:41:13,627
Here! Have a drink!

300
00:41:14,798 --> 00:41:18,867
No more wine for us please. We can't afford it

301
00:41:18,868 --> 00:41:20,967
It's alright

302
00:41:20,968 --> 00:41:24,707
This one's on me

303
00:41:24,709 --> 00:41:29,648
You're indeed a beautiful serpent

304
00:41:32,649 --> 00:41:35,248
Every day I carry those damn logs
without getting paid properly

305
00:41:35,249 --> 00:41:37,588
Now I'm so broke that even my hounds
look down on me

306
00:41:38,858 --> 00:41:41,057
We're losing our hunting grounds

307
00:41:41,058 --> 00:41:44,397
and you still keep the hounds
to look down on you?

308
00:41:44,398 --> 00:41:45,197
Look!

309
00:41:45,198 --> 00:41:47,527
Those are the trees
that used to watch over our ancestors

310
00:41:47,528 --> 00:41:49,497
This is how they end up

311
00:41:50,868 --> 00:41:54,967
Strange thing is, why so many constructions?

312
00:41:54,968 --> 00:42:00,377
What? Not only do you befriend us with wine
but you speak our language fluently

313
00:42:02,248 --> 00:42:03,677
Hey! It's going to rain

314
00:42:03,678 --> 00:42:07,387
Stop drinking and go home!
-Good morning, sir!

315
00:42:07,389 --> 00:42:09,288
Good morning, Mr. Policeman

316
00:42:11,288 --> 00:42:13,757
You've worked all day long
for such a mean wage

317
00:42:13,758 --> 00:42:17,857
and you waste it on wine?

318
00:42:17,859 --> 00:42:21,628
What else can we do with so little money?

319
00:42:21,628 --> 00:42:24,697
Yeah, right! We're savages, aren't we?

320
00:42:24,698 --> 00:42:27,637
We aren't supposed to know
anything about saving money

321
00:42:27,638 --> 00:42:31,477
Yeah, Mr. Policeman. You're Japanese, sir

322
00:42:31,478 --> 00:42:34,207
You don't know how hard our lives are

323
00:42:34,208 --> 00:42:37,817
Only Mr. Wu here understands us

324
00:42:37,818 --> 00:42:40,387
He's a beautiful serpent

325
00:42:40,388 --> 00:42:42,977
He's a viper!

326
00:42:45,488 --> 00:42:47,027
Excuse me -Hello

327
00:42:47,029 --> 00:42:49,258
I'd like some salt, please -No problem

328
00:42:52,898 --> 00:42:57,937
Oh no! It's raining! Hurry up and go home, sir

329
00:42:57,939 --> 00:43:00,868
Or your glorious uniform will be soaking wet

330
00:43:01,868 --> 00:43:03,207
Go ahead!

331
00:43:03,209 --> 00:43:04,638
Go on!

332
00:43:10,748 --> 00:43:12,217
Run, sir!

333
00:43:12,218 --> 00:43:15,237
Your Japanese fur is too precious to spoil

334
00:43:26,268 --> 00:43:27,927
It's raining

335
00:43:27,928 --> 00:43:31,237
Go collect the laundry hanging outside

336
00:43:31,238 --> 00:43:35,437
Can't you tell what needs to be done first?

337
00:43:35,438 --> 00:43:38,877
Hey, come back!
Are you taking the baby out in the rain?

338
00:43:38,878 --> 00:43:40,367
I'm sorry

339
00:43:48,048 --> 00:43:51,417
What an imbecile!

340
00:43:51,418 --> 00:43:53,477
Who'd marry such an idiot like you?

341
00:43:54,458 --> 00:43:55,927
When it rains, it pours

342
00:43:55,928 --> 00:43:57,287
Good morning

343
00:43:58,098 --> 00:44:00,127
This is our policeman Hanaoka Jiro

344
00:44:00,128 --> 00:44:02,967
This is our new police minister Ekawa Hakudo

345
00:44:10,178 --> 00:44:12,577
Jiro is a savage too

346
00:44:36,838 --> 00:44:38,137
Older brother

347
00:44:38,138 --> 00:44:40,137
Older sister -Older sister

348
00:44:40,138 --> 00:44:42,307
Younger brother -Younger brother

349
00:44:42,308 --> 00:44:43,977
Younger sister -Younger sister

350
00:44:43,979 --> 00:44:46,738
Okay, one more time

351
00:44:48,348 --> 00:44:50,477
Father -Father

352
00:44:50,478 --> 00:44:52,787
Mother -Mother

353
00:44:52,788 --> 00:44:55,047
Older brother -Older brother

354
00:44:55,048 --> 00:44:56,207
Older sister..

355
00:45:05,798 --> 00:45:07,857
Hurry! She's in labor!

356
00:45:09,868 --> 00:45:13,197
Two savages
can never give birth to a Japanese child

357
00:45:17,238 --> 00:45:18,477
Are you alright, Hanako?

358
00:45:18,479 --> 00:45:19,708
This job is for women only. What are you doing?

359
00:45:19,708 --> 00:45:22,237
Dakis, get out of here! Get out!

360
00:45:38,858 --> 00:45:41,417
Oh, what an extraordinary sight!

361
00:45:48,109 --> 00:45:49,628
Timber!

362
00:45:58,419 --> 00:46:01,248
(Hark, people)

363
00:46:01,249 --> 00:46:04,148
(Behold, people)

364
00:46:10,498 --> 00:46:15,297
(Oh, our warriors)

365
00:46:15,298 --> 00:46:20,137
(The youngsters
much like the budding pine leaves)

366
00:46:20,138 --> 00:46:24,707
(They show true bravery)

367
00:46:24,708 --> 00:46:27,007
(Fought in the falling leaves)

368
00:46:27,008 --> 00:46:29,277
(Fought under the withered pine tree)

369
00:46:33,418 --> 00:46:37,557
(Now they're back with heads hunted)

370
00:46:37,558 --> 00:46:42,117
(Our warriors fought with all their might)

371
00:47:02,048 --> 00:47:05,347
(Mahebu Police Station)

372
00:47:41,088 --> 00:47:42,207
Chief!

373
00:47:43,918 --> 00:47:47,887
Pawan, why aren't you in school?

374
00:47:47,888 --> 00:47:49,187
I'm sick

375
00:47:49,188 --> 00:47:52,487
Sick? But you don't look like sick

376
00:47:55,699 --> 00:47:57,428
Did your teacher beat you?

377
00:48:03,138 --> 00:48:06,597
I raced a Japanese kid and I won

378
00:48:07,478 --> 00:48:10,177
And the kid was crying

379
00:48:11,178 --> 00:48:16,547
The teacher blamed me for bullying him,
so he beat me

380
00:48:19,058 --> 00:48:21,217
Can I have another one please?

381
00:48:25,458 --> 00:48:28,867
I'll win the race on the sports day

382
00:48:28,868 --> 00:48:34,927
Those Japanese kids can cry their balls out
when they watch me getting awarded

383
00:48:43,848 --> 00:48:46,777
Chief, I hate the Japanese

384
00:49:28,258 --> 00:49:29,757
Chief Mouna?

385
00:49:29,758 --> 00:49:34,717
My grandpa said you were a hero
when you were younger

386
00:49:37,598 --> 00:49:40,627
Your grandpa said
I was a hero when I was younger?

387
00:49:41,608 --> 00:49:44,767
I'm still a hero. Does he know that?

388
00:50:08,629 --> 00:50:13,568
Chief Mouna, will you take me along
next time you go hunting?

389
00:50:18,478 --> 00:50:22,607
Pawan, where is your hunting ground?

390
00:50:27,249 --> 00:50:28,338
Chief Mouna!

391
00:50:56,778 --> 00:51:01,007
I'm alright. Just a little bit tipsy, that's all

392
00:51:02,888 --> 00:51:05,117
What the hell?

393
00:51:21,868 --> 00:51:22,767
Hanako!

394
00:51:32,348 --> 00:51:33,747
Look what you have done!

395
00:51:33,749 --> 00:51:38,188
How many times do I have to tell you
that you cannot drag these logs along?

396
00:51:38,919 --> 00:51:43,758
You destroyed the logs
-Only the bark is scratched

397
00:51:43,758 --> 00:51:45,227
The inside is still intact

398
00:51:46,098 --> 00:51:46,727
You savages!

399
00:51:46,729 --> 00:51:48,498
How many times do I have to tell you?

400
00:51:53,908 --> 00:51:56,877
What? You wanna fight?

401
00:51:56,878 --> 00:51:58,477
The paths are slippery because of rain

402
00:51:58,478 --> 00:52:04,107
He nearly lost his life slipping down a slope

403
00:52:05,619 --> 00:52:07,848
Where is your log?

404
00:52:09,448 --> 00:52:12,177
Slipped into the ravine -Slipped?

405
00:52:14,958 --> 00:52:18,897
Do you know how expensive it is?

406
00:52:20,528 --> 00:52:21,757
Pihu!

407
00:52:25,638 --> 00:52:26,757
Yoshimura!

408
00:52:31,508 --> 00:52:32,737
Chief Mouna..

409
00:52:38,618 --> 00:52:40,277
Sir Yoshimura?

410
00:52:41,118 --> 00:52:43,317
You're looking at me
at such a disrespectful angle

411
00:52:43,318 --> 00:52:46,307
Aren't you afraid of being stabbed blind?

412
00:52:51,698 --> 00:52:54,257
Who do you think you are?

413
00:52:56,199 --> 00:53:00,658
You're not the boss here in Mehebu

414
00:53:01,938 --> 00:53:03,267
I am!

415
00:53:15,648 --> 00:53:17,277
You will not get paid today

416
00:53:20,658 --> 00:53:24,387
The precious logs are destroyed

417
00:53:26,098 --> 00:53:29,027
Do it again and you'll have to pay for the loss

418
00:53:29,728 --> 00:53:32,037
Keep working! -With what?

419
00:53:32,038 --> 00:53:35,767
We get nothing from working for you

420
00:53:35,769 --> 00:53:38,008
What do you want us to pay with? -Pihu!

421
00:53:38,008 --> 00:53:41,147
Chief Mouna, he... -I saw it

422
00:53:41,149 --> 00:53:42,508
Go home!

423
00:53:43,548 --> 00:53:44,567
Go home!

424
00:53:55,688 --> 00:53:59,497
Yoshimura, stop picking on them

425
00:53:59,498 --> 00:54:01,427
You don't know nothing

426
00:54:03,338 --> 00:54:05,357
I was educating them

427
00:54:29,928 --> 00:54:31,947
These damn savages!

428
00:54:40,938 --> 00:54:42,627
I'll have you pay for this some day

429
00:55:02,588 --> 00:55:03,497
Good morning

430
00:55:03,499 --> 00:55:04,618
Good morning

431
00:55:07,098 --> 00:55:09,327
Good morning

432
00:55:09,328 --> 00:55:11,767
What? Checking out guns?

433
00:55:11,769 --> 00:55:15,298
Watan Robo is getting married
We've got some preparations to do

434
00:55:16,538 --> 00:55:18,377
Tado? Baso?

435
00:55:18,378 --> 00:55:20,777
I heard your father Mouna Rudo

436
00:55:20,778 --> 00:55:24,477
has mobilized lots of men for this hunt?

437
00:55:26,448 --> 00:55:30,487
Yeah, but what can we hunt
in those disappearing forests?

438
00:55:30,489 --> 00:55:33,148
You've about hacked down all the trees
on our hunting grounds

439
00:55:33,988 --> 00:55:36,087
If we don't go hunting now

440
00:55:37,498 --> 00:55:40,327
we'll have nothing left
once the trees are all gone

441
00:55:40,328 --> 00:55:41,727
Tado Mouna!

442
00:55:43,299 --> 00:55:44,958
You'd better watch your mouth!

443
00:55:54,608 --> 00:55:56,597
Savages will always be savages

444
00:55:58,818 --> 00:56:00,177
They have no manners at all

445
00:56:15,868 --> 00:56:16,727
Wait!

446
00:56:18,568 --> 00:56:19,367
Pawan?

447
00:56:20,138 --> 00:56:21,537
What is the kid doing there?

448
00:56:28,178 --> 00:56:29,307
Pawan!

449
00:56:57,338 --> 00:57:01,067
Chief Mouna! My hunting ground is right here!

450
00:57:21,468 --> 00:57:22,957
Temu Walis?

451
00:57:30,079 --> 00:57:31,908
You red-foot pheasant!

452
00:57:31,908 --> 00:57:34,437
Don't you know
this is the Mehebu hunting ground?

453
00:57:35,049 --> 00:57:38,718
Mouna! It's just a misunderstanding

454
00:57:38,718 --> 00:57:41,717
This is the first time my eldest son goes hunting

455
00:57:41,718 --> 00:57:44,087
I asked Temu to bring me here

456
00:57:45,258 --> 00:57:48,657
Mouna, I asked Temu to teach him

457
00:57:48,659 --> 00:57:51,418
Even so, you cannot trespass
into our Mehebu hunting ground

458
00:57:52,428 --> 00:57:54,297
This used to be our Toda hunting ground

459
00:57:55,228 --> 00:57:58,627
when my uncle was alive

460
00:57:59,568 --> 00:58:01,107
You Mehebu clansmen robbed it from us

461
00:58:01,108 --> 00:58:04,597
Rob it back if you can -Enough!

462
00:58:13,148 --> 00:58:16,347
Mouna, can you do me this favor?

463
00:58:17,489 --> 00:58:19,148
Favor?

464
00:58:19,718 --> 00:58:20,777
Kojima..

465
00:58:21,828 --> 00:58:25,317
if you lived in Mehebu now, I'd do you this favor

466
00:58:26,328 --> 00:58:28,397
But you live in Tnbarah Clan

467
00:58:28,399 --> 00:58:31,368
Take these red-foot pheasants
and get out of my hunting ground

468
00:58:37,578 --> 00:58:40,247
I don't care if it's your hunting ground or theirs

469
00:58:40,248 --> 00:58:42,937
because everything here
belongs to us Japanese now

470
00:59:16,409 --> 00:59:19,518
Temu, you just wait and see

471
00:59:19,518 --> 00:59:21,417
Some day I'll destroy your Tnbarah Clan

472
00:59:26,418 --> 00:59:29,047
Go on and do it if you dare

473
00:59:30,058 --> 00:59:33,257
Let's see who's killed first

474
00:59:43,408 --> 00:59:46,037
I don't care if you're Mouna Rudo

475
01:00:15,638 --> 01:00:17,407
Wow, well done

476
01:00:17,409 --> 01:00:20,568
Can a girl carry such a heavy load?

477
01:00:21,748 --> 01:00:23,277
Go! Go!

478
01:00:23,278 --> 01:00:25,877
Good girl!

479
01:00:25,878 --> 01:00:29,617
The men in your clan
are all out hunting, aren't they?

480
01:00:29,618 --> 01:00:31,557
Wanna make some extra bucks?

481
01:00:31,558 --> 01:00:33,417
Come with me to my boardinghouse! -No!

482
01:00:33,419 --> 01:00:35,148
I'll give you two dollars -No!

483
01:00:36,528 --> 01:00:38,087
What the hell? Bastard!

484
01:00:42,298 --> 01:00:45,097
Sir Sugiura, how dare you!

485
01:00:45,098 --> 01:00:48,467
Harassing a Mehebu woman?

486
01:00:49,339 --> 01:00:52,378
I was offering her a chance to earn
some extra money in our substation

487
01:00:52,378 --> 01:00:54,107
It's no big deal

488
01:00:54,108 --> 01:00:59,517
I know you Japanese policemen too well

489
01:00:59,518 --> 01:01:03,187
Take that blind prey of yours and scram

490
01:01:03,188 --> 01:01:04,987
It's true, and she accepted it too

491
01:01:04,989 --> 01:01:08,528
Another word from you
and I'll have the hounds feast on you

492
01:01:08,528 --> 01:01:10,757
Phooey! Fine, fine

493
01:01:12,028 --> 01:01:14,857
It's hard to reason with you savages

494
01:01:23,038 --> 01:01:27,667
You deserve it! Chicken!

495
01:01:42,589 --> 01:01:44,558
You're back, Sapu

496
01:02:00,038 --> 01:02:02,767
Chief, the matches you wanted

497
01:02:03,449 --> 01:02:05,348
Sapu?

498
01:02:05,351 --> 01:02:09,249
Let the kids eat more meat. They're too skinny
